<HEADLINE> Sihanouk Optimistic About Cambodia's Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SIEM REAP, CAMBODIA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian King
Norodom Sihanouk said Friday that he was optimistic about the
general elections to be held in July.
</P>
<P>
"I believe that the Cambodian people are able to organize the
elections in spite of the difficulties they face," the king told
foreign diplomats at his residence.
</P>
<P>
The king said he hoped that the international community would
continue to give his country support and help ensure a free and
fair election.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that national reconciliation was the basis for
peace, adding that the country could achieve national
reconciliation with a concerted effort by the Cambodian people.
</P>
<P>
On Pol Pot's death, Sihanouk said he believed Pol Pot had died,
saying even if he was not dead, he could not play any role.
</P>
</TEXT>
