<HEADLINE> Li Ruihuan Stresses Role of Non-Public Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, said today that various economic sectors should be
encouraged and developed to ease employment pressure.
</P>
<P>
While making an inspection in Wenzhou, booming city in east
China's Zhejiang Province, Li, a member of the Standing Committee
of the Political Bureau of the Chinese Party of China Central
Committee, praised local officials and the masses for exploring a
proper path of building socialism with Chinese characteristics
over the past years.
</P>
<P>
Wenzhou has a total population of seven million, however, it
has worked hard to provide jobs to one million local people who
used to be engaged in agriculture.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the city has attracted one million workers from
other parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
The achievements should be attributed to the booming of
non-public businesses, he said.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan noted the non-public ownership constitutes an
important component of China's socialist market economy. To make
public ownership as the mainstream and let diversified ownership
develop is the basic economic system in the primary stage of
socialism, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
