<HEADLINE> Iraqi FM Arrives in Cairo for Talks With Mubarak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Iraqi Foreign Minister Mohammed
Saeed Al-Sahhaf arrived here Friday for talks with President Hosni
Mubarak and Arab League Secretary General Esmat Abdel-Meguid, the
Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi News Agency (INA) said al-Sahhaf will be acting as
President Saddam Hussein's special envoy while meeting with
Mubarak. No details of his mission were available.
</P>
<P>
Al-Sahhaf told reporters that he would deliver a letter from
Iraqi President Saddam Hussein to Mubarak, but he did not
elaborate.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister will then travel on to New York where he
will watch closely the half-yearly review within the U.N. Security
Council of a report submitted by the U.N. Special Commission
(UNSCOM) overseeing the elimination of Iraq's weapons of mass
destruction.
</P>
<P>
The seven-year-old crippling U.N. sanctions against Iraq can
only be lifted after the UNSCOM certifies that Baghdad has scrapped
all prohibited weapons.
</P>
<P>
According to the INA, al-Sahhaf will meet representatives of
some members of the Security Council to discuss the latest
development in Iraq's relationship with the United Nations.
</P>
</TEXT>
