<HEADLINE> French Police Arrest Italian Right-wing Extremist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 17 (Xinhua) -- French police on Friday arrested an
Italian right-wing extremist hunted for years under an
international arrest warrant.
</P>
<P>
Carlo Cicuttini, 50, who had been a militant with the
extreme-right Ordine Nuovo Party and the fascist Italian Social
Movement, was arrested outside a small hotel in the suburb of the
southern city of Toulouse, said Agence France-Presse (AFP).
</P>
<P>
Cicuttini was accused by Italian judicial authorities of
murdering three military policemen in 1972 and was condemned in
absentia to imprisonment for life in 1987.
</P>
<P>
He was arrested in Spain in 1985, but was released later
despite a request for extradition to Italy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
