<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 4 Israeli Soldiers, 1 Lebanese Wounded in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Four Israeli soldiers and one
Lebanese civilian were wounded Friday during Lebanese guerrilla
attacks in south Lebanon, Lebanese Voice of the People radio
reported.
</P>
<P>
The four Israelis were injured when their Shigif stronghold
inside the so-called Israeli security zone in south Lebanon was
hit by guerrilla rockets, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese Shiite Muslim "Amal" Movement led by the country's
House Speaker Nabih Berry claimed responsibility for the attack.
</P>
<P>
The attack raised to 43 the number of Israeli soldiers wounded
in south Lebanon since the beginning of this year. Another four
had been killed.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the Israeli allied South Lebanese Army said a
Lebanese civilian was also wounded by a mortar shell that was fired
toward an Israeli outpost at the village of Kaokab inside the zone.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the day, the Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of
God, carried out attacks on the Israeli position at Barashit
inside the occupied zone, the radio said. No casualties were
reported.
</P>
<P>
In retaliation for the attack, Israeli artillery later shelled
south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Since Israel set up a 1,200-square-kilometer self-declared
security zone in south Lebanon in 1985 with the aim of protecting
its northern settlements from Lebanese guerrilla cross-border
attacks, clashes between the Israeli troops and Lebanese
resistance fighters have never stopped. 
</P>
</TEXT>
