<HEADLINE> Two More Canadian Banks Announce Merger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The Canadian Imperial Bank of
Commerce and Toronto-Dominion Bank announced a merger Friday, the
second in recent weeks in Canada.
</P>
<P>
The deal comes close on the heels of the January announcement
of the corporate marriage of the nation's biggest and third
biggest banks, the Royal and the Bank of Montreal.
</P>
<P>
But both deals are still waiting for approval from the federal
government.
</P>
<P>
The two banks have combined assets of 460 billion Canadian
dollars (322 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Their merger will create the second largest bank in Canada and
the 10th largest in North America in terms of market
capitalization. 
</P>
