<HEADLINE> Tanzanian President to Visit Zimbabwe Next Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian President Benjamin
William Mkapa will start a three-day state visit to
Zimbabwe on April 22 at the invitation of Zimbabwean
President Robert Mugabe.
</P>
<P>
The Zimbabwean Ministry of Foreign Affairs Friday said in a
statement that the two heads of state will hold talks on how to
strengthen and broaden bilateral cooperation in other
fields.
</P>
<P>
"The visit will build on the excellent political relations to
intensify economic ties," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Mkapa is expected to officially open the 39th Zimbabwe
International Trade Fair in Zimbabwe's second largest city of
Bulawayo on April 24.
</P>
<P>
Relations between Zimbabwe and Tanzania date back to the time
of Zimbabwe's liberation struggle when Tanzania provided
material, political and diplomatic support for Zimbabwe's
freedom fighters. 
