<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China-ASEAN Senior Officials Consultation Held in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The two-day fourth
China-ASEAN Senior Officials Consultation ended Friday and the
meeting focused on ways to realize the outcome of the China-ASEAN
Informal Summit held here last December.
</P>
<P>
During the consultation, the two sides agreed to expand
cooperation in the fields of economy and trade, investment as well
as science and technology to promote the Sino-ASEAN
good-neighborly partnership of mutual trust towards the 21st
century, a Chinese official attending the consultation told Xinhua
at the end of the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also discussed the economic and financial
situation in Asia and agreed that favorable conditions exist for
economic development in Asia and the current difficulties faced by
Asia are only temporary, the official said.
</P>
<P>
He said both sides are fully confident of the future of Asia's
development.
</P>
<P>
Both sides were also of the view that the consultation was
frank, friendly, fruitful and successful, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said ASEAN (Association of Southeast Asian Nations) member
countries spoke highly of China's important contribution to
stabilizing the regional financial situation by committing not to
devalue its currency and by extending financial assistance to
countries affected by the financial turmoil in Asia.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed to exchange views and coordinate on how to
strengthen regional financial cooperation and reforms as well as
to improve the international economic and financial order.
</P>
<P>
At the consultation, both sides also briefed each other on
their respective developments and exchanged views on regional and
international issues of mutual concern.
</P>
<P>
At the consultation, Chinese delegation leader and assistant
foreign minister Chen Jian backed ASEAN in continuing to play an
active role in regional affairs, and expressed satisfaction over
the development of the friendly relations between China and ASEAN
since China became a full dialogue partner of the regional
grouping.
</P>
<P>
Chen reiterated China's consistent stand that China wishes to
strengthen the good-neighborly and friendly relations with its
neighboring countries. He said the friendly relationship between
China and ASEAN not only has a solid foundation but also enjoys
the prospect of multi-level multi-sectoral development.
</P>
<P>
Chen said that to strengthen mutually beneficial cooperation
between China and ASEAN conforms to the interests of the people
of China and that of each ASEAN country.
</P>
<P>
Chen also said China had adopted a very active approach towards
overcoming the financial crisis in East Asia. In this regard,
China, though itself a developing country, is ready as a member of
Asia to continue to make concrete efforts for alleviating the
difficulties affecting the regional economy, he said.
</P>
<P>
Chen stressed that what China has been doing to help the
countries to overcome their difficulties is without any condition
and China is never seeking any reciprocation. China only hopes to
see further development in the region on the basis of peace and
stability, he said.
</P>
<P>
The China-ASEAN Senior Officials Consultation is an important
part of the mechanism for the full dialogue partnership and is
held once a year. The consultation is attended by senior officials
at the deputy minister level from China and ASEAN members --
Brunei, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar, the Philippines,
Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
Senior officials from all ASEAN members and the ASEAN secretary
general attended the consultation in Malaysia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
