<HEADLINE> 2.5 Million Nigerians Infected With AIDS/HIV </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's Health Minister Jibrila
Ayinla has warned against the alarming rate at which the HIV/AIDS
infection is spreading in the west African country.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a news conference in Abuja Friday, the minister
disclosed that an estimated 2.5 million Nigerians are already
infected with AIDS/HIV virus, while 1,400 new infections are
occuring everyday.
</P>
<P>
According to the minister, about 80 percent of the total
infections were through sexual transmission, though blood
transfusion is also a common mode of transmission.
</P>
<P>
Ayinla said that his ministry, with assistance from the
federal government, will organize a massive awareness campaign
for the civil servants from April 21 to 22.
</P>
<P>
The campaign, he said, is necessary because of the high degree
of complacency, cynicism and apathy among the public.
</P>
<P>
As part of the campaign, civil servants will be given lectures
on the facts and fictions of HIV/AIDS infections, he added.
</P>
