<HEADLINE> Romania: New Government Sworn in to Office </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The new cabinet of Romania was
sworn in to office Friday, two days after it's validation by the
Parliament.
</P>
<P>
The new cabinet, headed by Prime Minister Radu Vasile, swore in
the Cotroceni Palace (Presidential Palace) to respect the
Constitution, to exert all their strength to insure the country
prosperity and the population happiness.
</P>
<P>
The new cabinet consists of 25 members: one prime minister, two
ministers of state, 23 ministers and one secretary of state with
the defense ministry. The positions of ministers of state are
filled concurrently by the defense minister and the justice
minister.
</P>
<P>
Vasile has already made clear in his ruling program that the
guiding principles for his cabinet would be: social reform for the
recognition and affirmation of moral values; property right; a
decent living standard; accelerated institutional reform; and the
restructuring and upgrading of industry to insure a lasting
economic growth; reorientation and development of agriculture; a
balanced distribution of the transition costs.
</P>
<P>
On April 2, President Emil Constantinescu officially authorized
the 55 year-old economist Radu Vasile, general secretary of the
largest National Peasant's Party in the coalition, to form a new
cabinet.
</P>
<P>
The former government, which was headed by Victor Ciorbea,
resigned on March 30 after failing to solve a government crisis.
</P>
