<HEADLINE> Sonia Starts National Campaign to Revitalize Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 17 (Xinhua) -- India's Congress President
Sonia Gandhi Friday announced a three-pronged strategy to
revitalize her party which had a poor showing in the
February-March general elections.
</P>
<P>
Sonia made the announcement at a public gathering in Motihari,
the east state of Bihar, on the first leg of her national campaign
to revitalize the Congress, according to the Press Trust of India.
</P>
<P>
The Congress had become weak as senior leaders lost direct
contact with the rank and file for years, Sonia said, adding that
one way to strengthen the party is to give proper attention to
grassroots workers.
</P>
<P>
"We have to take fundamental steps to infuse new strength in
the party," she told 25,000 supporters at the rally.
</P>
<P>
"Without total identification with the common worker, breathing
fresh life into the organization would remain a distant dream,"
she said.
</P>
<P>
The second step is to win back minority communities that lost
trust in the party, and the third is to give more power to women.
</P>
<P>
Sonia started talking with Congressmen soon after taking over
as president of the party, and has already met leaders of almost
all the parties in both houses of parliament.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
