<HEADLINE> Two Bombs Explode in Virginia Towns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Two bombs exploded outside a
home and a restaurant in Virginia Friday morning, critically
injuring a woman and burning two men, the Associated Press
reported.
</P>
<P>
The two men, a father and son in Mineral, about 60 kilometers
northwest of Richmond, picked up a tackle box in their driveway.
when they brought it inside and opened it, the bomb went off and
burned the men on their arms.
</P>
<P>
The second bomb was found about 16 kilometers away in the
parking lot outside a Pizza Hut in downtown Louisa.
</P>
<P>
The explosion injured a woman, who was listed in critical
condition at a medical center.
</P>
<P>
A young lady was killed in December when an explosive device
detonated outside her apartment in Louisa, about six blocks from
the restaurant explosion, the report said. 
</P>
