<HEADLINE> Eritrea, Ethiopia Embark on New Stage: President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Eritrean President Isaias
Afwerki has said that Ethiopia and Eritrea are embarking upon a
new stage of cooperation, the Ethiopian News Agency reported
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Isaias made the announcement in an interview with ASER, an
Ethiopian magazine published in Tigrigna language, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
According to the president, the two countries are now moving
toward a new stage of cooperation which will have a significant
bearing on their economies.
</P>
<P>
The policies which now appear to be incompatible will
eventually be in tune after the two countries have passed through
the new stage, the president noted, adding that the condition on
the ground now will serve the purpose of testing the viability of
the policies exercised in both countries.
</P>
<P>
The government of Eritrea is against the application of the
Letter of Credit (LC) and the use of foreign currency to conduct
transactions because it is of the opinion that such a procedure
is incompatible with the reality on the ground, the president
said.
</P>
<P>
Biltateral ties remain good despite the new policies
implemented by Addis to safeguard its own interests which he said
do not imply a shift of stance on the part of the Ethiopian
People's Revolutionary Democratic Front (EPRDF) or the Ethiopian
government regarding relations with the Eritrean people and the
state, the report said.
</P>
<P>
In an earlier issue, ASER carried a statement by Ethiopian
Premier Meles Zenawi on the use of Letter of Credit and hard
currency in transactions between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Meles underlined in his statement that the new policy will
equally benefit buyers as well as traders, the news agency
reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
