<HEADLINE> Mkapa Hails Zimbabwe's Independence Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 17 (Xinhua) -- President Benjamin Mkapa
Friday reaffirmed his government's determination to enhance and
consolidate the cordial relations and close cooperation between
Tanzania and Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
Mkapa made the remarks in a congratulatory message sent to
Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe, whose country will celebrate
the 18th anniversary of independence Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In a statement released by the Foreign Ministry, Mkapa said
Tanzanians will join their brothers and sisters of Zimbabwe
Sunday in celebrating the historic occasion to remember the
heroic struggle for liberation from the colonial powers.
</P>
<P>
Mkapa is the third president of Tanzania, following Julius
Nyerere and Ali Hassan Mwinyi. Relations between the two
countries date back to the time of Zimbabwe's liberation struggle
when Tanzania provided materials, political and diplomatic
support for Zimbabweans fighting for freedom and independence.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
