<HEADLINE> Fuzhou Railway Station Explosion Kills Three </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, April 18 (Xinhua) -- A powerful explosion rocked the
Fuzhou Railway Station in southeastern Fujian Province at 06:00 am
on Friday morning, claiming the lives of three people and injuring
six, two of whom are still in serious condition.
</P>
<P>
Eyewitness reports indicate that a passenger's luggage exploded
between two coaches. Railway authorities and local police arrived
at the scene immediately to begin rescue efforts.
</P>
<P>
The injured were transported to a nearby hospital, and local
police agencies are currently investigating the cause, according
to local officials.  
</P>
