<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong International Film Festival Closes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The curtain went down for the
22nd Hong Kong International Film Festival (HKIEF) following the
screening of the film "Sweet Generation" by a Taiwanese director
Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the closing ceremony, Chairman of the Cultural
Activities Sub-committee of the Provisional Urban Council Jennifer
Chow Kit-bing said that during the 16-day festival over 260 films
were shown.
</P>
<P>
Archival treasures and the latest film production, including
films that were nominated or had won awards at different film
festivals, were shown this year. Special themes like "Song and
Dance in Indian Cinema", "History in the Making: Hong Kong 1997"
were featured.
</P>
<P>
While the screenings came to an end, the Hong Kong Film Archive
Treasures Exhibition at the Hong Kong City Hall will continue
until April 26. 
</P>
</TEXT>
