<HEADLINE> Chinese Women Prove Strength in Vancouver World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 18 (Xinhua) -- China women proved their strength
in the first day of the two-day Sagit Cup tournament on Friday in
Vancouver, Canada.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese women dominated Friday's competition as Bi Wenjing
won the women's balance team and the uneven bars and Kui Yuanyuan
won the vault, leaving the floor exercise the only one missed.
</P>
<P>
Romania's Simona Amanar won the floor exercise event and
finished second in the balance beam, which was also won by Bi.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Jinjing highlighted only in the men's event for Chinese
gymnasts to win the pommel horse event, while Huang Xu came second
behind Russian Alexei Nemov in the floor exercise.
</P>
<P>
Russia's Alexer Bonderenko won the men's vault, narrowly
beating Huang.
</P>
<P>
Bonderenko shared the victory with Greece's Dimosthenis Tabakos
in the men's rings event.
</P>
<P>
Slovenia's Aljaz Pegan won the horizontal bar while Jesus
Carballo of Spain won the parallel bars. 
</P>
