<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jordan's Stock Market Turnover Rises by 46.9 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The turnover at Jordan's stock
market in the past trading week amounted to 4.7 million Jordanian
dinars (about 6.63 million U.S. dollars), the Jordan Times
newspaper reported on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted the weekly bulletin of the Amman Financial
Market as saying that the total turnover from April 11 to 15
witnessed a rise of 46.9 percent from that in the trading week
from April 4 to 5.
</P>
<P>
The increase was made possible due to the publication of good
achievements in 1997 of several major industrial companies and
their announcement to distribute dividends to the shareholders,
according to the semi-official newspaper.
</P>
<P>
The turnover rise last week was also owed to a normal trading
week compared with the previous one, which was cut short to two
trading days due to Muslim holidays.
</P>
<P>
But as the average daily turnover is concerned, it is lower
last week, whose amount stood at 940,000 dinars (about 1.33
million dollars) compared to 1.6 million dinars (2.26 million
dollars) in the previous week.
</P>
<P>
The industrial sector got lion's share in last week's trading
of up to 42.1 percent while the service sector ranked the second
with a share of 28.2 percent, according to the newspaper. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
