<DOCNO> XIE19980418.0084 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-18 13:49 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Palestinian Protesters Clash With Israeli Soldiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Several hundred Palestinian
protesters clashed with Israeli soldiers Saturday in East
Jerusalem, but there was no reports of casualties so far.
</P>
<P>
The clash took place in Salah A-Deen Street, when the
palestinians are protesting for the Palestinian prisoners detained
in Israeli jails on the Palestinian prisoners Day Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Israeli soldiers and security forces closed off the street
while tension continues there.
</P>
<P>
There are two type of Palestinian prisoners detained in
Israeli jails. Most of them are held under the administrative
detention without any charges and others are under criminal
charges.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian side put the total figure of Palestinians held
in Israeli jails at over 3,000.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, the Israeli Defense Force released Ahmed
Katamesh, 45, leader of the Popular Front for the Liberation
of Palestine arrested on September 1, 1992 and transferred to
administrative detention in october 1993.
</P>
<P>
Saturday's protest was the first one held this year by the
Palestinians in East Jerusalem, which the Israelis claim as its
sole capital. Israeli soldiers and security force have put East
Jerusalem under tight security control for fear of unrest
there. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
