<HEADLINE> Pak Prime Minister to Visit Italy, Belgium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif will make an official visit to Italy and Belgium from April
19 to 24, the Associated Press of Pakistan (APP) reported
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
During his visit to Italy from April 19 to 22, the first ever
by a Pakistani Prime Minister, Sharif will hold formal talks with
his Italian counterpart Romano Prodi.
</P>
<P>
Sharif is also is expected to participate in the Investment
Conference jointly sponsored by Pakistan's Board of Investment and
the Italian Chamber of Commerce.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan and Italy will make efforts to identify areas for
mutual cooperation in economic relations. During the visit, a
number of agreements are also expected to be signed between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
While in Belgium, Sharif will hold formal talks with Belgium
Prime Minister Jean-Luc Dehaene.
</P>
<P>
To enhance economic interaction with Belgium, an Agreement for
the Promotion and Protection of Investments will be signed during
the visit.
</P>
<P>
The Pakistani Prime Minister will address an Investment
Conference, which will be attended by a large number of Belgian
entrepreneurs.
</P>
<P>
The APP report said that Sharif's visit to Italy and Belgium
will provide a strong impetus to the traditionally warm and
cordial ties between Pakistan and the two European countries.
</P>
