<HEADLINE> Dalian Export Commodity Trade Fair Gains National Status </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The Dalian Export Commodity
Trade Fair will become a national event starting from next year,
according to the fair's organizing committee.
</P>
<P>
Committee representative made the remarks today during the
ongoing 83rd China Export Commodities Trade Fair in Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
The Dalian fair, approved by the Ministry of Foreign Trade and
Economic Cooperation, will be sponsored jointly by the China
Chamber of Commerce of Importers and Exporters of Machinery and
Electronics Products, the China Chamber of Commerce of Importers
and Exporters of Metals and Mineral and Chemical Products and
various local governments.
</P>
<P>
Previous fairs were under the sole sponsorship of local
governments.
</P>
<P>
However, this year's fair will include exhibition halls for
machinery, electronics, metals, minerals and chemical products, as
well comprehensive exhibition halls.
</P>
<P>
Organizers of the Dalian fair will invite foreign trade
companies and export commodity manufacturers from throughout the
country, especially enterprises in the machinery, electronics,
metals, minerals, and chemical products sectors.
</P>
<P>
China currently offer seven local trade fairs, with the annual
Dalian fair, first held in 1987, scheduled to run from July 15-21.
</P>
<P>
The 11 previous fairs have yielded a total export volume of
five billion US dollars, with economic and technological
cooperation projects involving total funding of three billion US
dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
