<HEADLINE> Macao Museum Inaugurated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The Macao Museum featuring the
cultural integration between the East and the West opened here
today.
</P>
<P>
Visiting Portuguese Prime Minister Antonio Guterres, Macao
Governor Vasco Rocha Vieira and Xinhua News Agency Macao Branch
Director Wang Qiren inaugurated the museum together.
</P>
<P>
With a total investment of 130 million patacas (about 16.25
million U.S. dollars), the museum has a floor space of 2,800
square meters, demonstrating articles and models dating back as
early as the neolithic age.
</P>
<P>
The museum also uses video and other electrical means to show
Macao's unique history, customs, people's daily life, traditional
arts and craft works, trade and different industries such as
candle and incense-making and casinos.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the museum has a temporary part that displays the
changes taken place in the 20th century as well as introduction to
Macao's future as a Special Administrative Region of China after
1999.
</P>
<P>
It is so far the most comprehensive museum in Macao. 
</P>
</TEXT>
