<DOCNO> XIE19980418.0101 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Assistance to HK Fish Farmers To Be Discussed at PLC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 18 (Xinhua) -- A special meeting of the
Finance Committee of the Provisional Legislative Council (PLC)
will be held next Thursday to consider government proposals for
providing financial assistance to fish farmers affected by the
recent red tides.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Economic Services Bureau said here today
that the proposals included an injection of 200 million HK dollars
(25.6 million U.S. dollars) into the Kadoorie Agricultural Aid
Loan Fund and an injection of 17 million HK dollars (2.2 million
U.S. dollars) into the Emergency Relief Fund.
</P>
<P>
The injection into these two funds is required so that they
would have sufficient capital to meet the needs of all farmers
affected, he said.
</P>
<P>
Fish farmers can apply under the Kadoorie Agricultural Aid Loan
Fund for low-interest loans. The size of the loan in any
individual case depends on factors such as the cost of fish fry
and the duration in raising the fish to marketable size, said the
spokesman.
</P>
<P>
Under the proposals, the loan amount will not exceed 500,000 HK
dollars (64,100 U.S. dollars), of which up to 100,000 HK dollars
(12,820 U.S. dollars) may be granted on an unsecured basis. The
interest rate on the loans will be 2 percent and repayment need
not commence until 18 months after the loan is drawn.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman added that the mariculture operators were also
eligible under the Emergency Relief Fund for grants of up to
11,250 HK dollars (1,442 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Most of Hong Kong fishing zones were affected by the red tides,
a build-up of algae, earlier this month, and preliminary estimates
put losses at over 80 million HK dollars (10.3 million U.S.
dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
