<HEADLINE> Capital Iron and Steel Co. Exports Plate Steel to Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The Capital Iron and Steel
Corporation recently exported 14,000 tons of medium and thick
gauge plate steel to France, Germany and various other major
European markets.
</P>
<P>
The recent plate steel exports were the first for the
Beijing-bases corporation, according to a company executive, who
noted that the company's traditional market was in Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
However, the shrinking market in Southeast Asia forced the
company to target its business promotions in European countries
which have a large demand for various gauges of plate steel. The
company is currently fulfilling orders for six European countries,
according to the official.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, the company's exports of construction-use steel
products is still inadequate. The International Trade and
Engineering Company, a subsidiary of the Capital Iron and Steel
Corporation, is extending great efforts to make the best use of
adjustments in relevant state policies to expand the scope of
imports and exports of general commodities and technical products.
</P>
<P>
The company's promotions and sales departments have introduced
wide-ranging products, including steel, metallurgical spare parts
and electromechanical products, as well as daily-use items to
businessmen from nations throughout the world. Related efforts
increased the corporation's exports of sideline products by 60
percent in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The corporation recorded a 1997 export sales volume of 1.5
billion yuan, with annual profits standing at 200 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Contracted projects in foreign countries have emerged into an
important component of overseas business, said one corporation
executive, adding the corporation has contracted overseas projects
valued at 100 million U.S. dollars, including a contract for
upgrading a blast furnace in Zimbabwe.  
</P>
</TEXT>
