<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Nepali Govt Wins Confidence of Parliament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The three-member new government
of Nepal led by Girija Prasad Koirala obtained a vote of
confidence Saturday afternoon with a comfortable majority in the
Lower House of parliament.
</P>
<P>
The government garnered 144 votes in the 205-seat Lower House,
41 more than needed to win a vote of confidence, as the main
opposition Communist Party of Nepal (United Marxism-Leninism,
CPN-UML) and the newly-formed National Democratic Party (RPP) both
threw their weight behind Koirala as they had promised.
</P>
<P>
Four MPs from two small parties voted against, while those from
other parties including the RPP led by former prime minister Surya
Bahadur Thapa abstained.
</P>
<P>
The government took office on Wednesday, comprising only Prime
Minister Koirala, Deputy Prime Minister and Minister for Water
Resources Miss Shailaja Acharya and Finance Minister Ram Saran
Mahat.
</P>
<P>
The Nepali Congress, the largest party in the House with 87
MPs, has decided to form a minority government after failing to
find a ruling partner.
</P>
<P>
Under the constitution, any coalition or minority government
must obtain a vote of confidence in the Lower House within 30 days
to remain in office. And if it fails, parliament must be dissolved
for fresh polls.
</P>
<P>
Observers said that the CPN-UML and New RPP have offered
support to the minority government led by the NC because they do
not want new elections under the present conditions.
</P>
<P>
They will be at a disadvantage as the government remains in
power for six months even after the fresh polls are called.
</P>
<P>
Koirala has decided to expand the cabinet after winning the
vote of confidence.
</P>
<P>
Surya Bahadur Thapa resigned on April 10 under a power-sharing
agreement he reached with the NC, one of his ruling partners.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
