<HEADLINE> Fifth Tianjin Spring Commodities Fair Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 18 (Xinhua)-- The Fifth Tianjin Spring
Commodities Fair, sponsored by the State Economic and Trade
Commission and Tianjin Municipality, opened today in Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
Trade delegations from 28 provinces, municipalities and
autonomous regions from throughout China are participating in the
fair. In addition, the Hong Kong Trade Development Council has
organized the participation of a number of companies from the
special administrative region.
</P>
<P>
The five-day fair features more than 2,400 booths spread over
50,000 square meters. A number of large domestic manufacturers and
conglomerates, as well as foreign-funded companies are exhibiting
products and undertaking extensive marketing activities at the
fair.
</P>
<P>
The fair, which is expected to attract over 150,000 visitors,
offers three comprehensive and three specialized exhibition halls
for building materials, imported motor vehicles and stockpiled
commodities.
</P>
<P>
Information concerning the fair and participating business
delegations is offered on the Internet, and business transactions
can be concluded within a year following the conclusion of the
event. 
