<HEADLINE> Zambia to Decentralize Mines Ministry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Zambia will decentralize the
Mines Ministry by creating four bureaux to manage mining affairs
to improve the viability of the mining sector.
</P>
<P>
Mines Minister Syamukayumbu Syamujaye said here Friday that
the bureaux will be set up in Mkushi, Kitwe, Chipata and
Livingstone respectively in the Lusaka, Copperbelt, Eastern and
Southern provinces, the Zambia Daily Mail reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The bureaux will provide technical services in geology,
mining, processing, safety and environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
They will also manage documentation pertaining to the
acquisition of mining rights, marketing and export procedures.
</P>
<P>
Syamujaye said the government is striving to promote
investment in the gemstone sub-sector, which is a potentially
viable area to exploit. 
</P>
