</P>
<P>
Speaking at a seminar on media and elections organized by
Baptist university, Clement Mak, acting secretary for
Constitutional Affairs, said that the Legislative Council
elections scheduled to be held in Hong Kong on May 24, the first
of its kind since the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR) was established last July, is of great significance.
</P>
<P>
Efforts will be further made by the government to ensure the
election arrangements fair, open, honest and acceptable to the
Hong Kong residents, he said.
</P>
<P>
In a bid to promote a publicity drive, the government has set
up an inter departmental working group composed of representatives
of the Constitutional Affairs and other departments as well as
Hong Kong Radio.
</P>
<P>
the publicity drive will focus on geographical constituencies
election and registered electors will be urged to cast their votes
actively.
</P>
<P>
As to the elections by functional constituencies and Election
Committee, Mak said that messages will be directly conveyed to the
relevant electors by adopting a strategy in accordance with the
actual situation.
</P>
<P>
He said the government will remind electors to cast their votes
on May 24, tell them about the close links between the work of
the Legislative Council and the citizens' life.
</P>
<P>
During the publicity drive, he said introductions will be given
on voting procedures, arrangements for every elections, functions
and composition of the Legislative Council as well as candidates
in varied ways.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, in commemoration of the first Legislative Council
elections of the HKSAR, the Special First Day Cover will be issued
a week before the elections. 
