<HEADLINE> Cambodian Prince to Give up Area Under His Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Deposed First Prime Minister
Prince Norodom Ranariddh will give back the area under the control
of the forces loyal to him, according to a statement received here
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
In the four-point statement released Friday, Ranariddh said
that he fully supports King Norodom Sihanouk's ceasefire proposal.
</P>
<P>
In addition to declaring a unilateral ceasefire, he said, he
will give back the area under the control of the troops loyal to
him.
</P>
<P>
The prince reiterated that neither he has had any cooperative
relations with the Khmer Rouge, nor have his troops had any
military links or cooperation with them.
</P>
<P>
In March, King Sihanouk requested his son to give back the
"autonomous zone" controlled by the forces loyal to him. He also
proposed to the Hun Sen government to reintegrate those troops
into one royal forces.
</P>
<P>
Ranariddh favored the proposal but denied that he had any
autonomous zones.
</P>
<P>
Under Cambodia's party law, those controlling autonomous zones
will be prohibited from participating in the elections. 
</P>
