</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- The Taliban militia and the anti-Taliban Northern
Alliance have agreed to hold face-to-face talks for the first time
in over a year, U.S. President's special envoy Bill Richardson
said here Friday evening.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a press conference here at the American Center after
a day-long visit to Afghanistan, Richardson said the Taliban and
the Northern Alliance agreed to hold the proposed talks scheduled
for April 27 in Islamabad. The two sides also agreed not to launch
new military offensives until they meet in face-to-face talks in
Islamabad later this month, he added. (Afghanistan-Agreement)
</P>
