</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. space shuttle Columbia after one-day delay
was launched into space Friday from Kennedy Space Center, Cape
Canaveral.
</P>
<P>
On its 25th flight, shuttle Columbia carried a seven-member
crew and a menagerie of more than 2,000 creatures,including
pregnant mice, rats, snails, fish and crickets. During the
two-week long flight, NASA scientists will conduct 26 biological
experiments called the Neurolab. It is their hope that these
experiments would provide the most in-depth study ever of the
brain and nervous system in space. The seven astronauts and
menagerie of animals will serve as the test subjects.
(Space-Shuttle-Columbia) 
</P>
