<HEADLINE> ICBC Beijing Branch to Issue Mortgage Loans for Individuals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) --The Beijing Branch of the
Industrial and Commercial Bank of China (ICBC) plans to issue 500
million yuan of loans this year to support individual residents to
buy their housing, China's leading newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
The branch has also published measures on management of
guaranty loans to individual recently, which has set clear
definitions on such issues concerning the status of future loan
users, loan line, terms and forms of repayment, the "People's
Daily" said.
</P>
<P>
By the end of March, the branch had altogether issued to
individuals such guaranty loans totalling 87.31 million yuan and
had helped urban residents buy 555 apartments, the paper added.
</P>
<P>
China will stop distribution of government-subsidized housing
as a welfare form later this year, and residents will have to buy
their own apartments through market as the country's housing
reform continues to expand in depth.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports said that the People's Bank of China, the
central bank, will issue some 100 billion yuan of loans for
housing this year, in a bid to encourage individual residents to
purchase their own flats.
</P>
<P>
It is also encouraging all commercial banks to provide
long-term mortgage loans if necessary.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that 58.7 percent of the housing sold from
January to November of 1997 went to individual buyers, an increase
of 27.7 percent over the same 1996 period.  
</P>
</TEXT>
