<HEADLINE> Shortest Int'l Shipping Route Operational in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, April 18 (Xinhua) -- A shipping route connecting Heihe
City of northeast China's Heilongjiang Province and
Blagoveshchensk of Russia has been commissioned recently.
</P>
<P>
The shipping route is considered the shortest in the world as
the straight distance between Heihe City and Blagoveshchensk is
just 25 km.
</P>
<P>
The two cities are separated by the Amur River or the
Heilongjiang River.
</P>
<P>
One single trip only takes 15 minutes, said a local official,
adding that the availability of the service will help speed the
customs clearance.  
