<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cuba Reports Low Rate of Accidents in Workplace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The number of workplace accidents
in Cuba stands at 8.1 per 1,000 workers, the lowest in Latin
America, an expert said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The average rate in Latin America exceeds 15 workers per 1,000
while five million persons die in the region every year due to
causes related to labor environment, according to the World Health
Organization.
</P>
<P>
Director of Cuba's National Institute of Work Medicine, Emidgio
Leo, said the state provides special care to workers in economic
areas with high risks, especially in mining, sugar, fishing and
agriculture sectors.
</P>
<P>
The director spoke at the third International Congress of the
Medical Association of the Caribbean, which was attended by more
than 600 experts from 23 countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
