<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania's New Cabinet Takes Oath of Office </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Romanian Prime Minister Radu
Vasile and his cabinet were sworn in office in the presidential
palace on Friday.
</P>
<P>
After the ceremony, President Emil Constantinescu said in a
speech that the government crisis in the past several months had
not only adversely influenced the reform process, but also
tarnished the country's image.
</P>
<P>
Constantinescu called on all parties to halt partisan
disputes and do a little more than they say.
</P>
<P>
The president said the main mission of the new cabinet is to
uphold reforms, adding that the cabinet is facing a difficult
situation and enormous pressures.
</P>
<P>
Constantinescu asked the government to resolve the country's
current economic setbacks in a "simple and effective" way.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday evening, Romania's parliament validated Vasile's
cabinet with a majority of 317 to 124 votes.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, President Constantinescu authorized Vasile,
general secretary of the largest National Peasant's Party in the
coalition, to form a new cabinet.
</P>
<P>
The former government, which was headed by Victor Ciorbea,
resigned on March 30 after failing to solve a government crisis.
</P>
</TEXT>
