<HEADLINE> Chile, U.S. Sign Trade Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Chile and the United States on
Friday signed an agreement on commercial cooperation to help
increase the flow of investment between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by Chilean Economy Minister Alvaro
Garcia, and U.S. Secretary of Commerce William Daley, during the
on-going state visit to Chile by U.S. President Bill Clinton.
</P>
<P>
Garcia said later that "Chile and the United States are in a
privileged moment of their commercial relationship, and the
proposed target is to take advantage of this development."
</P>
<P>
Daley said the agreement is one more example of the
rapprochement the two countries are undergoing.
</P>
<P>
The aim of this agreement is to expand the commercial accords
already in place and to provide a better living standard for the
people of Chile and the United States, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
