<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Production of Household Electric Appliances more Centralized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Production of China's household
electric applicances are becoming more centralized, industry
sources said.
</P>
<P>
According to State Statistics Bureau (SSB), in 1997, the six
largest Chinese producers of refrigerators, washing-machines,
air-conditioners, and freezers accounted for 75 percent, 74.58
percent, 68.47 percent, and 81.8 percent of the country's total
output, respectively.
</P>
<P>
An SSB report shows that the production scale of a number of
household electric appliances have been up with their large
overseas counterparts. For example, the output of the single
product of 17 enterprises has exceeded one million sets. Of them,
the output of the Rongsheng and Haier refrigerators and washing
machines, Rongshida washing machines, and Little Swan washing
machines surpassed 1.5 million sets.
</P>
<P>
A survey on 72 household electric appliances producers
indicates their combined sales value amounted to 74.58 billion
yuan (about 8.985 billion US dollars). Among them, 20 enterprises
generated a combined sales value of 58.9 million yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
