<HEADLINE> CCPIT Receives 7,000 Overseas Business Groups </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The China Council for Promotion
of International Trade (CCPIT) received over 7,000 overseas
business delegations in the last six years.
</P>
<P>
Over 100 delegations CCPIT received were those accompanying
heads of state or government in their China visits.
</P>
<P>
CCPIT sponsored seminars or talks for these delegations.
</P>
<P>
Chinese leaders met with 260 such delegations, according to Yu
Xiaosong, CCPIT president.
</P>
<P>
In his report to a recent CCPIT conference, Yu said that from
1992 to 1997, CCPIT organized 3,000 Chinese business delegations
to visit 50 countries and regions, 15 of which accompanied the
visits of Chinese leaders.
</P>
<P>
He said that the tours have helped Chinese businesses struck
deals with overseas companies valued at billions of US dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
