<HEADLINE> Colombo Stock Market Turnover Up By 100 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The Colombo stock market had
increased its turnover by over 100 percent during the first three
months of this year compared to the corresponding period of 1997,
the stock market sources said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The sources said domestic and foreign turnover at the Colombo
Stock Exchange (CSE) during the first three months amounted to
74.2 million U.S. dollars, up 119 percent from 33.9 million
dollars in the same period of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Local investors continue to dominate the market accounting for
over 50 percent of the turnover and 90 percent of trades executed
during the first quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
Stock broking sources attributed the good performance to
impressive corporate earnings, improved investor confidence due to
the buoyancy of the economy as well as stabilizing situation in
South East Asia. These factors also have attracted greater foreign
investor interest into the market, the sources pointed out.
</P>
</TEXT>
