<HEADLINE> CCPIT Improves Its Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The China Council for the
Promotion of International Trade (CCPIT) improved its services to
Chinese and overseas businesses in the last six years.
</P>
<P>
From 1992 to 1997, CCPIT handled over 30,000 overseas patent
applications and 70,000 trade marks applications, said Yu
Xiaosong, CCPIT president, at a recent meeting.
</P>
<P>
He told the CCPIT meeting that during this period, CCPIT also
heard over 300 cases of patent and trade mark infringement.
</P>
<P>
The arbitration organization affiliated with CCPIT accepted
3,292 international economic and trade arbitration cases and 72
maritime arbitration cases, and 2,793 and 69 such cases have been
wound up, respectively, Yu said.
</P>
<P>
The CCPIT also issued 1.16 million general certificates of
origin in the period.  
</P>
</TEXT>
