<HEADLINE> Venezuelan President Leaves for Summit of Americas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Venezuelan President Rafael
Caldera left here Friday for Chile to attend the Second Summit of
the Americas to be held on April 18-19.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-four leaders from the South American continent will
attend the summit to negotiate the establishment of the Free Trade
Area of Americas (FTAA) by the year 2005.
</P>
<P>
Venezuelan Foreign Ministry sources said that Venezuela will
present proposals at the summit for regional energy cooperation
and strengthening democracy and human rights.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation on regional energy includes the creation and
improvement of regulatory systems and the promotion of legal,
fiscal and regulatory frameworks to encourage national and foreign
investment in the energy sector and other related sectors.
</P>
<P>
President Caldera will make an official visit to Peru after
attending the summit of the Americas. 
