<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 63 Tamil Rebels Arrested in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Sixty-three cadres of the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) have been arrested by the
security forces while a few others have surrendered in the past
two days, a local newspaper reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The arrests have been made by the forces engaged in the ongoing
Jaya Sikuru (Certain of Victory) operation in Mankulam and
Kilinochchi areas in Northern province of the country.
</P>
<P>
According to some disclosures made by the rebel cadres, a
number of LTTE rebels who are in a state of frustration now, are
making preparations to surrender, a senior army officer was quoted
as saying.
</P>
<P>
The officer told the paper that the LTTE rank and file are
completely demoralized due to shortage of man power and other
shortcomings they are experiencing at present.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE have been fighting a 15-year war against the
government for a separate Tamil state in the north and east of the
country.
</P>
<P>
The latest round of Jaya Sikuru operation was launched by
government troops to open a key supply line along the highway
Vavuniya to the Jaffna Peninsula in the north of the island
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
