 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- China's longtime official pricing system on cotton has been
abolished as the government has decided to adopt an indirect
control over the field. Under the new policy, the government will
only issue guiding prices for cotton and the market will play a
bigger role in pricing.
</P>
<P>
-- Li Ruihuan, Chairman of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference, said Friday
that various economic sectors should be encouraged and developed
to ease employment pressure. Li made the remark while making an
inspection tour of Wenzhou, a booming city in east China's
Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
-- Vice-Premier Li Lanqing met Friday with scholars from
China's inland areas and the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (HKSAR), attending a hi-tech symposium in the Chinese
capital, and hoped that they would increase cooperation and
achieve good progress.
</P>
<P>
-- The State Development Planning Commission and the State
Statistics Bureau recently announced a real estate and housing
price index for the first time and decided to make similar
announcements on a regular basis beginning from this year.
</P>
<P>
 "China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The red tide wreaking havoc in aquaculture zones in Hong
Kong and Guangdong Province in the last few days has not yet
extended to neighboring Fujian Province or other areas, said a local
official in charge of fishery environment supervision.
</P>
<P>
-- The first inter-Korean government talks are at a standstill
again, according to the Republic of Korea's chief delegate Jeong
Se-hyun.
</P>
<P>
-- The China's Central Government has vowed to enable 3.5
million young and middle-aged Chinese illiterates to learn to read
and write this year.  
