<HEADLINE> Casio to Demo New Mega Pixel Digital Camera </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Casio, Inc., a major Japanese
electronic company, announced in its New Jersey venture Friday
that it will demonstrate Casio's new QV-5000SX true mega pixel
digital camera during the upcoming COMDEX show, Chicago, Illinois,
on April 20-23, 1998.
</P>
<P>
The new QV-5000SX will be available later this spring with an
estimated street price of 599 U.S. dollars, the company said. The
camera features 1.3-million-pixel CCD, Auto Focus, 2X/4X digital
zoom, an optical viewfinder, built-in 4-mode flash, and other
powerful features and functions, it said.
</P>
<P>
The new camera allows the user to select either 32, 48 or 64
frames, both at 0.1-second intervals and play them back on the
camera as a movie or save them on to a PC and use the included
software to make 3.2, 4.8 or 6.4 second movies at 10fps.
</P>
<P>
The camera has a panorama recording and playback feature. It
allows you to create 360 degree panorama picture by using the
panorama guide feature. Both movies and panoramas can be recorded
and played back using the camera itself, without the need of any
special options or additional software.
</P>
<P>
The 1.3-million-pixel high-definition CCD outputs to a computer
measure 1,280 by 960 dots. This results in images of outstanding
detail and definition and near photographic quality for printouts.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
